  "prompt": "How much is the typical home owner insurance?",
  "response": "The cost of homeowners insurance varies widely depending on several factors, including:\n\n1. Location\n2. Home's value\n3. Construction type\n4. Coverage amount\n5. Deductible\n6. Credit score\n7. Claims history\n\nOn average in the United States, homeowners insurance typically ranges from:\n\n- $300 to $1,500 per year\n- Around $1,200 is considered a typical annual premium\n\nFactors that can increase cost:\n- High-risk areas (hurricanes, wildfires)\n- Older homes\n- Expensive homes\n- Lower credit scores\n- Previous insurance claims\n\nFactors that can decrease cost:\n- Home security systems\n- Good credit\n- Bundling with auto insurance\n- Higher deductibles\n\nFor the most accurate estimate, it's best to get quotes from multiple insurance providers specific to your home and location.",
